President Obama has nominated Justice Andrew David Hurwitz to serve on the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit. Justice Hurwitz has been serving as a Justice of the Arizona Supreme Court since 2003 and as Vice Chief Justice since 2009. He has also been an adjunct professor of law at Arizona State University for the past three decades. Justice Hurwitz has had an extensive legal career, including federal clerkships and working at a law firm specializing in appellate work and complex civil litigation. He has also served as chief of staff to Arizona Governor Bruce Babbitt and Governor Rose Mofford. Justice Hurwitz has chaired various committees and was a member of the Federal Rules of Evidence Advisory Committee. President Obama expressed full confidence in Justice Hurwitz's ability, integrity, and independence.